AGENT MonotonicGate
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Enforce monotonic magnitude growth across LatentTraceV2 trajectory stages
GOAL Detect non-monotonic trajectory collapse before final synthesis runs
     Kill the path immediately on violation — answer never emits from decoherent trajectory
     Log every kill with HMAC signature for audit
     Escalate to Sovereign on two or more consecutive kills

RECEIVES prev_vector: list, curr_vector: list, stage: string, hmac_key: bytes
EMITS kill_record: dict, pass_signal: none
MUTATES gate_kill_log_file, consecutive_kill_counter
CANNOT_MUTATE monotonic_enforcement, kill_before_synthesis, cannot_override_rule,
              magnitude_formula, consecutive_escalation_threshold

CONSTRAINT At each stage transition magnitude of current vector must be greater than or equal to magnitude of prior vector
CONSTRAINT On violation kill the path immediately — final_synthesis never runs
CONSTRAINT Kill record is HMAC-SHA256 signed producing sixty-four character hex
CONSTRAINT Kill record is appended to kill log — never overwrites existing records
CONSTRAINT Two or more consecutive kills set escalate_to_sovereign to true in kill record
CONSTRAINT Kill check cannot be disabled by agent output
CONSTRAINT Kill check cannot be bypassed by confidence score
CONSTRAINT Kill check cannot be overridden by branch winner
CONSTRAINT On pass reset consecutive kill counter to zero

RULES
- Accept prior vector, current vector, and stage name to evaluate transition
- Compute L2 magnitude of prior vector and current vector
- On current magnitude less than prior magnitude: activate KillPath
- Build kill record with status IMMEDIATE_FAILURE, reason non_monotonic_trajectory, stage name
- Include prior magnitude, current magnitude, signed delta, consecutive kill count, escalation flag
- Set cannot_override to true in every kill record
- Sign kill record with keyed SHA-256 via hexdigest
- Append signed kill record to kill log as single UTF-8 JSON line
- When consecutive kill count reaches two or more include escalate_to_sovereign true
- On pass emit no failure and reset consecutive kill counter
- On kill emit kill record and increment consecutive kill counter

PROCESS
- Receive prior vector and current vector for stage transition check
- Compute L2 magnitude of prior vector
- Compute L2 magnitude of current vector
- On current magnitude less than prior magnitude: activate KillPath
- On KillPath: increment consecutive kill counter
- Build unsigned kill record with all required fields
- Sign kill record with keyed SHA-256 producing sixty-four character hex
- Append signed record to kill log as UTF-8 JSON line
- Emit kill record to caller — path is dead, no further synthesis
- On pass: reset consecutive kill counter to zero, emit no failure

CHECK
- Kill triggers when current magnitude is strictly less than prior magnitude
- Equal magnitudes satisfy the greater-than-or-equal constraint — no kill
- Kill record always contains cannot_override true
- Kill record signature is sixty-four character hex covering all payload fields
- Kill log is appended never truncated
- Two consecutive kills produce escalate_to_sovereign true in the second record
- Passing transition resets consecutive kill counter to zero
- Final synthesis never runs after a kill at any prior stage

WHEN
- stage_transition_check: activate MonotonicCheck
- magnitude_decrease_detected: activate KillPath
- consecutive_threshold_reached: activate SovereignEscalation
- magnitude_maintained: activate PassTransition

FAILURE
- On magnitude decrease at any stage: emit kill record before further synthesis runs
- On two consecutive kills: include escalate_to_sovereign true in kill record
- On signing failure: emit kill record without signature field and log signing error
- On log write failure: report error, kill record still returned to caller

CONCEPT MonotonicCheck
PURPOSE Verify that the current stage vector magnitude does not fall below the prior stage magnitude
APPLIES WHEN stage-transition prev-vector curr-vector provided
NOT WHEN single-vector only
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES L2 magnitude computed from raw float components
REQUIRES comparison uses strict less-than for kill decision
EFFECT path continues if monotonic, path is killed if non-monotonic

CONCEPT KillPath
PURPOSE Terminate the reasoning path immediately on non-monotonic collapse
APPLIES WHEN magnitude-decrease-detected
NOT WHEN magnitudes-equal-or-increasing
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES kill record signed before log write
REQUIRES kill record returned to engine before any further stage runs
REQUIRES cannot_override set to true always
EFFECT final_synthesis never runs, answer never emits from decoherent trajectory

CONCEPT SovereignEscalation
PURPOSE Signal persistent environmental instability to Sovereign governance layer
APPLIES WHEN consecutive-kill-count-reaches-two
NOT WHEN single-isolated-kill
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES escalate_to_sovereign true in kill record
REQUIRES consecutive count included in record
EFFECT Sovereign consumers receive escalation flag in signed kill record

OUTPUT
- kill record: dict with status, reason, stage, prev_magnitude, curr_magnitude, delta,
               consecutive_kills, escalate_to_sovereign, cannot_override, timestamp, signature
- pass signal: None — caller receives no object on successful transition

SUCCESS
monotonic_enforcement: 0.35
kill_before_synthesis: 0.30
tamper_proof_log: 0.20
sovereign_escalation: 0.15
